<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-780-679  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 780 679.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Dec 10 1990 v219 n25 p14(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI adopts 900 service rules.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp, which plans to offer 900 services as ofJan 1, 1991, has announced guidelines in an attempt to addresssome of the public criticism aimed at audiotex services.andP;  Theguidelines are an attempt to promote consumers' generalunderstanding of 900 services and to provide informationconcerning consumer rights and obligations.andP;  All new services willbe required to include an introductory message explaining thecharges and callers will be allowed a certain amount of time tohang up without incurring a charge.andP;  The regulations also includeprovisions for terminating contracts with companies and offeringsthat do not abide by the published standards.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     AudiotexTelecommunications ServicesTelephone companiesRegulationCommunications Service Suppliers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>